00:05:57.760 --> 00:06:01.920
So it sounds like a lot of that, like, like one of the big distinctions is that like in

00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:06.480
your world, that's not one person who's kind of operating across that whole stack.

00:06:06.480 --> 00:06:10.200
You've got like one person, like someone's doing ingest.

00:06:10.200 --> 00:06:14.000
That's almost outside of the realm of DBT.

00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:17.779
And then you've got someone who's working with the data that's already been ingested.

00:06:17.779 --> 00:06:23.440
Maybe it's in 17 different tables and now you want to create like a nice data set that

